sentences: Ki Hui-hyeon (Korean: 기희현; Hanja: 奇熙賢; born June 16, 1995), better known by the mononym Huihyeon and former stage name Cathy, is a South Korean singer-songwriter, rapper and actress.

Shortly after debut with the group in December 2015, MBK Entertainment announced she had temporarily withdrawn from the group, along with her bandmate Jung Chae-yeon, to represent MBK Entertainment on reality girl group survival show Produce 101 for the chance to debut in a Mnet girl group.
On May 11, 2016, MBK Entertainment confirmed that she and Jung Chae-yeon had re-joined DIA.
On August 17, it was announced that Ki would be collaborating with I.O. I members Choi Yoo-jung and Jeon So-mi for the digital single, "Flower, Wind and You", which was produced by Boi B.
In 2016, she also appeared on Mnet's rap survival program Unpretty Rapstar 3 as a contestant.

In September 2019, Ki participated in the survival program show, V-1, to select the Vocal Queen among the various girl group members, where only the top 12 girl group members in votes would progress and perform on the show.
